Following the abduction of school students and staff from Government Science College Kagara in Rafi Local Government, Governor Abubakar Bello has stated that he won’t tender his resignation.  The Governor said this after some groups made a public call for him to resign over the abduction. Responding to calls for his resignation while addressing newsmen today February 19, Bello averred that he is not considering it as this is the first time such an incident is happening. He Said; “I am not considering resigning anything. This is the first time students are being kidnapped in this state”.  Source Renowned Islamic Scholar, Sheikh Abubakar Gumi, on Friday, met with the Governor of Niger State, Abubakar Bello, over the abduction of students and members of staff of Government Science College, Kagara. Photos of Gumi meeting with some bandits in a forest in Niger State surfaced online on Friday. The Islamic… In "News" Abubakar Sani Bello, the Governor of Niger State, has said his administration will not pay ransom to kidnappers, The PUNCH reports. Bello said this following the abduction of some students and staff of Government Science College in Kangara, Rafi Local Government Area of Niger State in the early hours of… In "Politics" Global rights group, Amnesty International, says the abduction of students and members of staff of Government Science College, Kagara, in Niger State, shows that the Federal Government is not doing enough to protect the lives of citizens. The PUNCH had reported that some students and staff of the school were… In "News"